        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Christ's explanation of his meaning only drew from Peter a more energetic asseveration of his constancy even unto death. \"He thought he was able,\" says St. Augustine, \"because he felt that he wished.\" The other apostles made a similar assertion, and Jesus said no more, leaving time to prove the truth of his sad foreboding. Matthew 26:35",
