  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Vincent's Word Studies",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Though I should die (κἂν δέῃ με ἀποθανεῖν)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The A. V. misses the force of δέῃ: \"Though it should be necessary for me to die.\" Wyc., \"If it shall behove me to die.\" Rev., excellently, \"Even if I must die.\" ",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
